{
  "texts": [
    "All ABCD computations are local, involving neighboring sections only.",
    "Within each block of sections, a section is aligned to the previous n sections considered by the Vector Voting procedure.",
    "When stitching blocks together, blocks do not interact with other blocks beyond the decay distance.",
    "Such locality enables graceful extension to petascale datasets, and the blocks can be processed in parallel by hundreds of distributed workers.",
    "At the same time, ABCD has several shortcomings."
  ]
}